info:
Produces a normalized tag map with quality metadata.

In production, replace this node with your protocol source (OPC UA, Modbus, MQTT, Sparkplug, etc.) and ensure its output follows the same tag map format:
```json
{
  "<tag.name>": { "value": <value>, "quality": "good", "units": "<unit>" }
}
```
Quality values: `good`, `bad`, `uncertain`, `stale`.
Bad or stale quality triggers the binding's `onBad` fallback and eventually the comm-loss banner.

func:
// Simulate oscillating tank level and pump run state
var t = Date.now() / 8000;
var level = 50 + 30 * Math.sin(t);
var running = level > 40;

msg.payload = {
    // Tank level — structured form with quality and units
    'TK01.level': { value: Math.round(level * 10) / 10, quality: 'good', units: '%' },
    // Pump run state — boolean tag
    'P101.run':   { value: running, quality: 'good' },
    // Pump amps — zero when stopped, random 8-12 A when running
    'P101.amps':  { value: running ? Math.round((8 + 4 * Math.random()) * 10) / 10 : 0, quality: 'good', units: 'A' }
};
return msg;
